There was a small chuckle of laughter over NIGHTSHIFT&#39;s radio, &quot;Ahh,
you are still living in your petty bickerings.&quot;

As the voice of the queen spoke the drone troopers brought NIGHTSHIFT
up to the highest level of CRYONOSIS, to an area that looked as if it
was once an observatory of some sort.

&quot;But don&#39;t you realize that some things have grown larger than you,
larger than even this planet?&quot; The voice sounded tired again. &quot;You are
such small creatures.&quot;

As NIGHTSHIFT and BATSCOUT arrived the room looked as if it had been
cleared out. On the floor Where once there should have been computer
banks and consoles, there was appeared to be a large honeycomb like
structure with a single large opening in the center of it.

It looked like a hive.

&quot;We have heard the calls.&quot; The queen&#39;s voice said. &quot;And now, at last,
we are ready to answer.&quot;

The hive like structure in the center of the room began to glow a
strange orange color and  began to pulse with power. Above the room
the ceiling of the room rumbled and then began to open, much like an
observatory might, letting in frigid winds from the outside and snow
began to whip around the room.

Outside the revealed skies looked dark and angry, lightning began to
strike as thunder boomed!

The twin insectile troopers stood silently watching NIGHTSHIFT and
BATSCOUT with cold impassive eyes seemingly immune to the chaos of the
snows and the storm.

